snippet: There were conflicting reports of American casualties after a suicide bomber crashed into a vehicle belonging to the United States Consulate in the northwestern city of Peshawar on Monday.
abstract: Suicide bomber rams his explosives-laden vehicle into a sport utility vehicle belonging to the United States Consulate in the northwestern city of Peshawar, Pakistan, in one of the most brazen attacks against Americans in the country in recent years; United States Embassy in Islamabad reports that two Americans and two Pakistani employees of the consulate were injured.

byline.original: By ISMAIL KHAN and SALMAN MASOOD
byline.contributor: Ismail Khan reported from Peshawar, and Salman Masood from Islamabad, Pakistan. Steven Lee Myers contributed reporting from Jakarta, Indonesia.

lead_paragraph: There were conflicting reports of American casualties after a suicide bomber crashed into a vehicle belonging to the United States Consulate in the northwestern city of Peshawar on Monday.
